Hawkins accident prevention program includes:

1. Procedures and training for handling chlorine during manufacturing of sodium hypochlorite;

2. Implement safety systems to manage risks identified during process hazard analysis;

3. Conduct necessary plant maintenance and inspections to ensure equipment is in good working order;

4. Vendor provided DOT approved railcars;

5. Adhere to OSHA workplace safety regulations;

6. Follow Chlorine Institute standards.

7. Members in good standings with National Association of Chemical Distributors



5-year Accident History:  There has not been an accident involving chlorine at this facility in the last 5 years.



Emergency Response:  In the event of a maintenance issue with chlorine equipment/railcar, employees are trained on how to detect the source of the issue and take appropriate action such as closing or tightening a valve.  If an accidental release should occur, this facility has a trained on-site hazmat team including proper equipment (SCBA and C-kits) to respond.  This facility also conducts annual meetings and training sessions with the local emergency planning committee and hazardous materials responders (Memphis/Shelby County Special Emergency Association) and the Memphis Local Fire Department to ensure everyone is aware of the hazards at this site.



Planned Changes:  While Hawkins desires to continually improve safety, there are no specific changes planned other than to continue compliance with industry standards and government regulations and our own commitment to "Think Safe! Be Safe!"
